CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 20, 1969, pg. 11, reads: "Nite Kap East...was the scene of a real swinging Press Party last Sunday when members of the radio, television and press attended a party to officially introduce singer Tim 'T. S.' Stevens. in first photo, the good-looking young singer (holding microphone) gets set to sing.  He is flanked by sensational organist Wende [Wendell] Byrd (left) and Carl Murphy, drums... - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Wendell Byrd on organ, Tim Stevens holding microphone, and Carl Murphy holding drumstick, posed on stage in Nite Kap East, Strip District
